00:32:36,650 --> 00:32:38,480
- Now, Howard...
- Harold.

487
00:32:38,690 --> 00:32:42,580
Harold. These may seem silly,
but your candor is paramount.

488
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:44,210
Okay.

489
00:32:44,690 --> 00:32:46,090
So.

490
00:32:48,300 --> 00:32:52,260
We know it's a woman's voice,
the story involves your death...

491
00:32:53,870 --> 00:32:55,640
...it's modern, it's in English.

492
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:58,640
I'm assuming the author
has a cursory knowledge of the city.

493
00:32:58,640 --> 00:33:01,580
- Sure.
- Okay, good.

494
00:33:04,280 --> 00:33:06,010
Question one:

495
00:33:06,210 --> 00:33:08,920
"Has anyone recently left
any gifts outside your home? "

496
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:10,480
Anything? Gum? Money?

497
00:33:10,690 --> 00:33:12,930
- A large wooden horse?
- I'm sorry?

498
00:33:13,020 --> 00:33:15,070
- Just answer the question.
- No.

499
00:33:15,220 --> 00:33:18,060
"Do you find yourself inclined
to solve murder mysteries...

500
00:33:18,060 --> 00:33:21,560
...in large, luxurious homes
to which...? " Let me finish.

501
00:33:21,660 --> 00:33:24,370
"To which you may or may not
have been invited? "

502
00:33:24,370 --> 00:33:25,560
No. No, no, no.

503
00:33:25,770 --> 00:33:28,790
All right. On a scale of one to 10...

504
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:33,110
...what would you consider the
likelihood you might be assassinated?

505
00:33:33,110 --> 00:33:34,080
Assassinated?

506
00:33:34,280 --> 00:33:38,410
One being very unlikely, 10 being
expecting it around every corner.

507
00:33:38,410 --> 00:33:41,140
- I have no idea...
- Okay. Let me rephrase.

508
00:33:41,980 --> 00:33:43,980
Are you the king of anything?

509
00:33:45,050 --> 00:33:46,290
- Like what?
- Anything.

510
00:33:46,290 --> 00:33:48,790
King of the lanes
at the local bowling alley.

511
00:33:48,790 --> 00:33:50,190
"King of the lanes"?

512
00:33:50,390 --> 00:33:54,460
- King of the lanes. King of the trolls.
- "King of the trolls"?

513
00:33:54,460 --> 00:33:58,760
Yes. A clandestine land
found underneath your floorboards.

514
00:33:58,970 --> 00:34:00,270
- Anything.
- No.

515
00:34:00,470 --> 00:34:02,530
No. That's ridiculous.

516
00:34:02,740 --> 00:34:06,480
Agreed. But let's start with ridiculous
and move backwards.

517
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:09,610
Now, was any part of you at one time
part of something else?

518
00:34:09,610 --> 00:34:11,920
Like do I have someone else's arms?

519
00:34:11,980 --> 00:34:15,220
Well, is it possible at one time
that you were made of stone...

520
00:34:15,220 --> 00:34:17,320
...wood, lye, varied corpse parts...

521
00:34:17,320 --> 00:34:19,890
...or earth made holy
by rabbinical elders?

522
00:34:19,890 --> 00:34:23,790
No. Look... I'm sorry. What do these
questions have to do with anything?

523
00:34:23,790 --> 00:34:26,130
The only way to find out
what story you're in...

524
00:34:26,130 --> 00:34:28,330
...is to determine what stories
you're not in.

525
00:34:28,330 --> 00:34:31,800
Odd as it may seem, I've just ruled out
half of Greek literature...

526
00:34:31,800 --> 00:34:34,100
...seven fairy tales,
10 Chinese fables...

527
00:34:34,100 --> 00:34:37,240
...and determined conclusively
that you are not King Hamlet...

528
00:34:37,240 --> 00:34:39,230
...Scout Finch, Miss Marple...

529
00:34:39,440 --> 00:34:43,100
...Frankenstein's monster,
or a golem.

530
00:34:48,250 --> 00:34:51,320
Aren't you relieved to know
you're not a golem?

531
00:34:51,320 --> 00:34:54,650
Yes, I am relieved to know
that I am not a golem.

532
00:34:54,860 --> 00:34:55,820
Good.

533
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:02,550
Do you have magical powers?

534
00:35:38,100 --> 00:35:40,480
May I ask what we're doing out here?

535
00:35:40,500 --> 00:35:44,030
- We're imagining car wrecks.
- I see.

536
00:35:45,370 --> 00:35:47,840
And we can't imagine
car wrecks inside?

537
00:35:47,840 --> 00:35:49,370
No.

538
00:35:50,210 --> 00:35:52,650
Did you know
that 41 percent of accidents...

539
00:35:52,650 --> 00:35:55,140
...occur in times
of inclement weather?

540
00:35:55,350 --> 00:35:57,730
So do 90 percent
of pneumonia cases.

541
00:35:57,820 --> 00:36:02,720
Really? Pneumonia.
That's an interesting way to die.

542
00:36:03,660 --> 00:36:06,290
But how would Harold
catch pneumonia?

543
00:36:06,500 --> 00:36:08,700
Have you written
anything new today?

544
00:36:08,700 --> 00:36:09,960
No.

545
00:36:10,170 --> 00:36:13,170
Did you read the poems I suggested,
or make a list of words...

546
00:36:13,170 --> 00:36:15,280
...buy new typing paper, anything?

547
00:36:15,340 --> 00:36:16,900
No, none of it.

548
00:36:18,270 --> 00:36:20,240
Sitting in the rain won't write books.

549
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:24,800
Well, that illustrates exactly how much
you know about writing books.

550
00:36:31,650 --> 00:36:32,810
What's this?

551
00:36:33,420 --> 00:36:35,930
It's literature on the nicotine patch.

552
00:36:37,130 --> 00:36:40,890
I don't need a nicotine patch, Penny.
I smoke cigarettes.

553
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:42,630
Well, it may help.

554
00:36:42,830 --> 00:36:45,960
May help? Help what?

555
00:36:46,440 --> 00:36:49,340
Help what, Penny?
Help write a novel?

556
00:36:49,540 --> 00:36:51,770
May help save your life.

557
00:36:52,110 --> 00:36:54,750
I'm not in the business of saving lives.

558
00:36:57,310 --> 00:36:59,340
In fact, just the opposite.

559
00:37:02,420 --> 00:37:04,720
- "What's your favorite word? "
- Integer.

560
00:37:04,720 --> 00:37:06,240
Good, good, good.

561
00:37:06,460 --> 00:37:08,580
"Do you aspire to anything? "

562
00:37:09,930 --> 00:37:12,490
- No.
- Conquer Russia?

563
00:37:12,700 --> 00:37:15,260
- Win a whistling contest?
- No.

564
00:37:15,460 --> 00:37:19,330
Harold, you must
have some ambition.

565
00:37:20,140 --> 00:37:23,730
- I don't think so.
- Some underlying dream. Think.

566
00:37:26,010 --> 00:37:27,500
Well...

567
00:37:28,640 --> 00:37:31,750
...I've always wanted my life
to be more musical.

568
00:37:32,050 --> 00:37:35,450
<i>- Like West Side Story?
- No.</i>

569
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:37,750
- Like...
- What?

570
00:37:37,950 --> 00:37:41,450
Well, I've always wanted to learn
to play the guitar.

571
00:37:43,860 --> 00:37:45,490
Okay.

572
00:37:47,330 --> 00:37:49,500
The last thing
to determine conclusively...

573
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:52,200
...is whether you're in a comedy
or a tragedy.

574
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:53,720
To quote Italo Calvino:

575
00:37:53,740 --> 00:37:57,210
"The ultimate meaning
to which all stories refer has two faces:

576
00:37:57,210 --> 00:38:00,640
The continuity of life,
the inevitability of death. "

577
00:38:01,040 --> 00:38:04,410
Tragedy, you die.
Comedy, you get hitched.

578
00:38:08,220 --> 00:38:10,390
Most comic heroes
fall in love with people...

579
00:38:10,390 --> 00:38:12,390
...introduced after the story
has begun.

580
00:38:12,390 --> 00:38:15,220
Usually people
who hate the hero initially.

581
00:38:15,220 --> 00:38:19,020
Although I can't imagine anyone
hating you, Harold.

582
00:38:19,230 --> 00:38:23,030
Professor Hilbert, I'm an IRS agent.

583
00:38:23,400 --> 00:38:24,590
Everyone hates me.

584
00:38:26,030 --> 00:38:27,290
Right, right. Good.

585
00:38:27,440 --> 00:38:31,810
Have you met anyone recently
who might loathe the very core of you?

586
00:38:31,810 --> 00:38:35,500
I just started auditing a woman
who told me to get bent.

587
00:38:36,150 --> 00:38:38,260
Well, that sounds like a comedy.

588
00:38:39,520 --> 00:38:41,350
Try to develop that.

589
00:38:43,150 --> 00:38:44,180
Four of these?

590
00:38:44,390 --> 00:38:46,520
You know, I didn't get my honey,
honey.

591
00:38:46,520 --> 00:38:50,220
Lulu, can you refill the honey
for Larry? Quarters also?

592
00:38:50,260 --> 00:38:51,850
That's my good boy.

593
00:38:52,060 --> 00:38:53,990
I'm adding some acorns.

594
00:38:54,460 --> 00:38:55,860
Mr Crick.

595
00:38:57,000 --> 00:39:00,630
You're here early.
Must have a lot of people to extort.

596
00:39:00,640 --> 00:39:02,500
No. No, just you.

597
00:39:03,870 --> 00:39:06,670
- Twig tea and banana bread.
- Yes, ma'am.

598
00:39:06,880 --> 00:39:10,550
Actually, it should only take the day to
make sure 22 percent is all you owe.

599
00:39:10,550 --> 00:39:14,440
Well, I won't be paying no matter
the percentage, Mr Crick.

600
00:39:14,480 --> 00:39:18,440
No, I know. But the percent
determines how big your cell is.

601
00:39:25,030 --> 00:39:26,860
You know, you can call me Harold.

602
00:39:26,860 --> 00:39:30,030
Yeah, I know. But I don't want to.

603
00:39:32,230 --> 00:39:33,640
This is for Ramona, honey.

604
00:39:33,640 --> 00:39:36,330
- Oh, thank you.
- You're very welcome.

605
00:39:36,970 --> 00:39:39,280
What is that?
What are you marking?

606
00:39:40,810 --> 00:39:42,330
Oh, this is nothing.

607
00:39:42,540 --> 00:39:45,670
Why don't we start
with your backup documents...

608
00:39:45,880 --> 00:39:48,550
...and the receipts
for the past three years.

609
00:39:48,550 --> 00:39:50,040
Sure.

610
00:39:58,730 --> 00:39:59,920
What's this?

611
00:40:01,330 --> 00:40:03,420
- My files.
- What?

612
00:40:03,630 --> 00:40:05,120
My tax files.

613
00:40:06,040 --> 00:40:07,740
You keep your files like this?

614
00:40:07,740 --> 00:40:10,540
No, actually I'm quite fastidious.

615
00:40:10,740 --> 00:40:14,270
I put them in this box
just to screw with you.

616
00:40:27,820 --> 00:40:31,160
- Hi.
- Hi. How are you?

617
00:40:32,300 --> 00:40:34,960
So how was it? Aruba.

618
00:40:35,160 --> 00:40:38,670
Ms Pascal? Can I just ask you
