650
00:43:00,480 --> 00:43:01,840
I really can't.

651
00:43:02,050 --> 00:43:05,380
Mr Crick, it was a really awful day.

652
00:43:06,280 --> 00:43:09,120
I know, I made sure of it.

653
00:43:09,620 --> 00:43:11,310
So pick up the cookie...

654
00:43:11,520 --> 00:43:13,650
...dip it in the milk...

655
00:43:13,860 --> 00:43:15,650
...and eat it.

656
00:43:40,220 --> 00:43:42,590
That's a really, really good cookie.

657
00:43:50,860 --> 00:43:53,570
So when did you decide
to become a baker?

658
00:43:53,930 --> 00:43:56,830
- In college.
- Oh, like a cooking college?

659
00:43:57,970 --> 00:44:01,100
I went to Harvard Law actually.

660
00:44:01,670 --> 00:44:06,800
- Oh, I'm sorry, I just assumed it was...
- No. No, it's fine. I didn't finish.

661
00:44:07,580 --> 00:44:09,550
- Did something happen?
- No.

662
00:44:10,950 --> 00:44:14,940
I was barely accepted.
I mean, really barely.

663
00:44:15,150 --> 00:44:18,490
The only reason they let me come
was because of my essay.

664
00:44:18,490 --> 00:44:22,510
How I was gonna make the world
a better place with my degree.

665
00:44:23,260 --> 00:44:27,990
Anyway, we would have to participate
in these study sessions...

666
00:44:28,200 --> 00:44:31,300
...my classmates and I,
sometimes all night long.

667
00:44:31,400 --> 00:44:35,230
And so I'd bake so no one
would go hungry while we worked.

668
00:44:35,340 --> 00:44:38,510
Sometimes I would bake all afternoon
in the kitchen in the dorm...

669
00:44:38,510 --> 00:44:42,540
...and then I'd bring my little treats
to the study groups...

670
00:44:42,750 --> 00:44:44,370
...and people loved them.

671
00:44:44,580 --> 00:44:45,840
Eat.

672
00:44:46,050 --> 00:44:50,310
I made oatmeal cookies,
peanut-butter bars...

673
00:44:50,790 --> 00:44:54,220
...dark-chocolate
macadamia-nut wedges.

674
00:44:54,420 --> 00:44:56,930
And everyone would eat
and stay happy...

675
00:44:56,960 --> 00:44:59,330
...and study harder
and do better on the tests.

676
00:44:59,330 --> 00:45:02,230
More and more people started
coming to the study groups...

677
00:45:02,230 --> 00:45:04,060
...and I'd bring more snacks.

678
00:45:04,270 --> 00:45:07,000
I was always looking
for better and better recipes...

679
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:12,530
...until soon it was ricotta cheese
and apricot croissants...

680
00:45:13,410 --> 00:45:15,930
...and mocha bars
with an almond glaze...

681
00:45:16,150 --> 00:45:20,780
...and lemon chiffon cake
with zesty peach icing.

682
00:45:21,880 --> 00:45:25,910
And at the end of the semester
I had 27 study partners...

683
00:45:26,120 --> 00:45:29,560
...eight Mead journals
filled with recipes...

684
00:45:29,760 --> 00:45:31,280
...and a D average.

685
00:45:32,230 --> 00:45:34,030
So I dropped out.

686
00:45:34,630 --> 00:45:37,370
I figured if I was gonna
make the world a better place...

687
00:45:37,370 --> 00:45:39,530
...I would do it with cookies.

688
00:45:44,370 --> 00:45:45,810
You like them?

689
00:45:47,310 --> 00:45:48,300
I do.

690
00:45:49,380 --> 00:45:51,180
I'm glad.

691
00:45:52,250 --> 00:45:54,690
Thank you for forcing me
to eat them.

692
00:45:55,080 --> 00:45:56,850
You're welcome.

693
00:46:02,120 --> 00:46:05,090
I should go. Oh, thank you.
For the cookies, I mean.

694
00:46:05,090 --> 00:46:07,060
- Why don't you take them home?
- Oh, no.

695
00:46:07,060 --> 00:46:09,310
- Oh, come on.
- No, really, please.

696
00:46:09,430 --> 00:46:12,670
- No, really, please.
- No, no, no. Really, please.

697
00:46:12,670 --> 00:46:14,730
I would like to, but I can't.

698
00:46:15,400 --> 00:46:17,140
- You can't?
- No, no, I mean...

699
00:46:17,140 --> 00:46:19,840
Because, see, it constitutes a gift.

700
00:46:20,180 --> 00:46:22,950
Actually I shouldn't have even had
those other ones, so...

701
00:46:22,950 --> 00:46:25,350
Okay. Well, I'm not
gonna tell anyone.

702
00:46:25,350 --> 00:46:28,190
- No. I know, but if you did...
- Well, I'm not going to.

703
00:46:28,190 --> 00:46:29,490
I know, but if you did...

704
00:46:29,490 --> 00:46:32,760
- What, you think I'm gonna call the...?
- No, no. I'll purchase them.

705
00:46:32,760 --> 00:46:35,880
I'm happy to purchase them.
How's that?

706
00:46:37,930 --> 00:46:40,330
And then there are no issues.

707
00:46:42,430 --> 00:46:44,660
- What?
- No.

708
00:46:44,870 --> 00:46:46,930
- Please.
- Just...

709
00:46:47,140 --> 00:46:49,050
- Why don't I just...?
- Go home.

710
00:46:49,170 --> 00:46:50,670
Really, it's not a big deal.

711
00:46:50,670 --> 00:46:52,800
Go home.

712
00:46:54,480 --> 00:46:55,840
Okay.

713
00:47:00,450 --> 00:47:01,750
Did you?

714
00:47:03,350 --> 00:47:06,350
You baked those cookies for me,
didn't you?

715
00:47:09,990 --> 00:47:13,560
You were just trying to be nice
and I totally blew it.

716
00:47:17,300 --> 00:47:20,530
This may sound like gibberish
to you...

717
00:47:23,040 --> 00:47:25,530
...but I think I'm in a tragedy.

718
00:47:56,140 --> 00:48:00,180
Professor Hilbert, I've totally failed
at the comedy-tragedy thing.

719
00:48:00,180 --> 00:48:02,550
In fact, I think she likes me even less.

720
00:48:02,550 --> 00:48:05,120
- I know, it's great.
- What do you mean?

721
00:48:05,580 --> 00:48:08,050
You've proved something else
entirely.

722
00:48:08,050 --> 00:48:11,710
The voice seems to be dependent
on actions you take.

723
00:48:12,820 --> 00:48:15,490
You reset your watch,
it says you reset your watch.

724
00:48:15,490 --> 00:48:17,490
You ride a bus,
it says you ride the bus.

725
00:48:17,490 --> 00:48:20,060
You brush your teeth,
it says you brush your teeth.

726
00:48:20,060 --> 00:48:24,090
It may be that you yourself
are perpetuating the story.

727
00:48:24,300 --> 00:48:27,960
- So I suggest we try something else.
